      "date": "2021-11-17 04:00:04.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAndreas,\nI agree this is more like a bandaid than fix.\nI think there are several problems:\n__ext4_xattr_set_credits() from upstream just enlarge the credit needed\nno matter if ea_inode is actually needed or not.\na xattr create only needs 10 vs 20 if ea_inode is needed and the xattr  can fit in 1 block.\n\ndt_find_or_create code path only declare create op,\nbut osd_create will set fid in inode ea, the credits were not reserved for the xattr set I think.\n\nthen in lustre the osd_dto_credits_noquota[DTO_XATTR_SET] is a fixed 14, should be consistent with ldiskfs, large when ea inode is used?(not related to this ticket)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
